result.text:
Português/English
No dia 13 de novembro, a Celebração do 15º Aniversário do Instituto Confúcio na Unesp e a cerimônia de inauguração da Exposição de “Poesia e Pintura da China” foram realizadas na Unesp. Cerca de 200 pessoas, incluindo dignitários, empresas, representantes da comunidade chinesa, mídia, professores e alunos do Instituto Confúcio, testemunharam juntos esse importante momento. 
No discurso do Cônsul Geral Yu Peng, elogiou as realizações excepcionais do Instituto Confúcio, parabenizando a parceria robusta entre a Unesp e a Universidade de Hubei, desejando ao Instituto Confúcio um futuro melhor e doando livros ao Instituto Confúcio em nome do Consulado-Geral. No evento, foram apresentadas obras de caligrafia e pintura chinesas criadas por artistas da Universidade de Hubei.
O Instituto Confúcio na Unesp, estabelecido em conjunto pela Universidade de Hubei e pela Unesp, foi inaugurado em  2008 e é o primeiro Instituto Confúcio no Brasil. Com um total de matrículas de mais de 28.000 alunos, recebeu o título de "Instituto Confúcio Avançado no Mundo" por diversas vezes.
-----------------------
The Unesp Confucius Institute celebrated the 15th anniversary of its inception on Nov 13. Rectors of Unesp and Hubei University, dignitaries, and around 200 other representatives from enterprises, local Chinese community, media and Confucius Institute faculty witnessed the memorable occasion. A Chinese calligraphy and painting exhibition was also unveiled during the event, showcasing more than 20 artworks specifically created by Hubei University artists for the occasion.
Mr. Yu Peng, Consul General of China in Sao Paulo, highly praised the outstanding achievements of the Unesp Confucius Institute over the years, hailed the strong partnership between Unesp and Hubei University and wished the Unesp Confucius Institute an even better future. He donated some books to the Unesp Confucius Institute on behalf of the Chinese Consulate. 
The Unesp Confucius Institute, jointly established by Hubei University and Unesp, was inaugurated in 2008 as the first Confucius Institute in Brazil. With a total enrollment of more than 28,000 students, it was dubbed as one of the best Confucius Institutes in the world.

A Trupe de Arte Dragão e Leão da Universidade de Hubei realizou uma apresentação bem-sucedida no Memorial da América Latina, em São Paulo, no dia 14 de novembro, em comemoração ao 15º aniversário do Instituto Confúcio na Unesp. O Sr. Yu Peng, Cônsul-Geral da China, comentou a importância de aumentar o entendimento mútuo entre os dois povos da China e do Brasil por meio de intercâmbios culturais.

----------------------------
The Dragon & Lion Art Troupe from Hubei University staged a successful performance at the Latin America Memorial in Sao Paulo on Nov 14 in celebration of the 15th anniversary of the Unesp Confucius Institute. Mr. Yu Peng, Consul General of China, emphasized the importance of enhancing mutual understanding between the two peoples of China and Brazil through cultural exchanges.
Around 1000 people attended the performance consisting of dragon & lion dance, martial arts, and Chinese folk instrumental music, etc, deeply enchanted by the story of Brazilian exchange students’ encounter with Chinese traditional culture.

On November 9, Deputy Consul General Tian Yuzhen attended the annual event of the Fudan-Latin America University Consortium. He presented the possibilities offered by the "Belt and Road" initiative for Latin American countries and exchanged ideas with participants on China-Brazil and China-Latin America relations.
